

LUMOTAG is a fusion of video game first-person shooters like Fortnite and arena-combat games like laser tag. The system consists of a blaster and ID tags worn by players, with a small server maintaining the game state. The blaster has an integrated HUD, annotating the image feed with game stats - such as hitpoints, name and avatar of any player in the crosshairs. The HUD also relays key game moments, showing a 3rd-person view when you're eliminated from play - and at night transitions to become your primary combat interface through built-in night-vision technology, enabling stealth scenarios. The blaster prototype has been designed from the ground up with optical performance as the top priority, addressing common issues faced by other camera-based entertainment - such as poor low-light response, motion blur, and limited visual range.

The system will appeal to those already engaged in group activities like axe-throwing, laser tag, combat archery, and go-karting, with kits available for sale or rental to commercial venues. The system integrates naturally with a league structure similar to online games like Fortnite, where users maintain a persistent profile loaded at each visit and can build their rating - encouraging repeat play.